{"id":"glorify","term":"Glorify","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>(1.) To make glorious, or cause so to appear (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 12:28\">John 12:28</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 13:31\">13:31</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 13:32\">32</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 17:4\">17:4</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 17:5\">5</a>).</p>\n<p>(2.) Spoken of God to “shew forth his praise” (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Corinthians 6:20\">1 Cor. 6:20</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Corinthians 10:31\">10:31</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["John 12:28","John 13:31","John 13:32","John 17:4","John 17:5","1 Corinthians 6:20","1 Corinthians 10:31"]}